# AOT Safety

Apply this rule when the project publishes with Native AOT (`scripts/publish-aot.sh`).

## Do

- Source-generated `System.Text.Json` (`JsonSerializerContext`)
- Explicit DI registration — no assembly scanning
- `ICommandHandler` / `IQueryHandler` interfaces (no MediatR)
- `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` only with justification when unavoidable

## Do not

- Runtime reflection over open types (`Type.GetType`, `Activator.CreateInstance` on unknown types)
- `dynamic`, Newtonsoft.Json, AutoMapper, MediatR
- New dependencies without verifying trim/AOT compatibility

Run `aot-compat-check` before handoff when adding dependencies or serialization code.

See [docs/dotnet-code-style.mdc](../../docs/dotnet-code-style.mdc) §6.
